The father of murdered bride Anni Dewani has today marked what would have been his daughter's 33rd birthday in a hospital bed after his arm was torn off in a freak accident.

Engineer Vinod Hindocha, 65, was fixing a lift when it plunged to the ground, ripping his right arm off. 

He underwent a 13-hour operation to reattach his limb after being airlifted to hospital in Gothenberg, Sweden.

Today, Mr Hindocha posted a picture on Facebook of himself with two nurses and wife his Nilam, a cake and treats to mark Anni's birthday. She was 27 when she was shot dead on her honeymoon in South Africa.

